<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Free">Free</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Several <a href="/wiki/R_(programming_language)" title="R (programming language)">R</a> packages fit MARS-type models:
<ul>
<li><code>earth</code> function in the <code><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/earth/index.html">earth</a></code> package</li>
<li><code>mars</code> function in the <code><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/mda/index.html">mda</a></code> package</li>
<li><code>polymars</code> function in the <code><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/polspline/index.html">polspline</a></code> package. Not Friedman's MARS.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Matlab code:
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cs.rtu.lv/jekabsons/regression.html">ARESLab: Adaptive Regression Splines toolbox for Matlab</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Python
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://orange.biolab.si/blog/2011/12/20/earth-multivariate-adaptive-regression-splines/">Earth - Multivariate adaptive regression splines</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://github.com/jcrudy/py-earth/">py-earth</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
