<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Hastie T., Tibshirani R., and Friedman J.H. (2009) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www-stat.stanford.edu/~tibs/ElemStatLearn"><i>The Elements of Statistical Learning</i></a>, 2nd edition. Springer, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780387848570" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-0-387-84857-0</a> (has a section on MARS)</li>
<li>Faraway J. (2005) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.maths.bath.ac.uk/~jjf23"><i>Extending the Linear Model with R</i></a>, CRC, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781584884248" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-1-58488-424-8</a> (has an example using MARS with R)</li>
<li>Heping Zhang and Burton H. Singer (2010) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/Recursive-Partitioning-Applications-Springer-Statistics/dp/1441968237"><i>Recursive Partitioning and Applications</i></a>, 2nd edition. Springer, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781441968234" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-1-4419-6823-4</a> (has a chapter on MARS and discusses some tweaks to the algorithm)</li>
<li>Denison D.G.T., Holmes C.C., Mallick B.K., and Smith A.F.M. (2004) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.stat.tamu.edu/~bmallick/wileybook/book_code.html"><i>Bayesian Methods for Nonlinear Classification and Regression</i></a>, Wiley, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780471490364" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-0-471-49036-4</a></li>
<li>Berk R.A. (2008) <i>Statistical learning from a regression persepective</i>, Springer, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780387775005" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-0-387-77500-5</a></li>
</ul>


